[Bolton is located in the Greater Manchester area. A description and map of the Greater Manchester area can be accessed at: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greater_Manchester_Urban_Area.

The Greater Manchester Urban Area is an area of land defined by the Office for National Statistics, consisting of the large conurbation that encompasses the city of Manchester and the continuous metropolitan area that spreads outwards from it, forming much of Greater Manchester in North West England. According to the United Kingdom Census 2001, the Greater Manchester Urban Area has a population of 2 240 230, making it the United Kingdom's 3rd most populous conurbation after the Greater London and the West Midlands urban areas. - Mod.CP]

