******
Africa
[4] Nigeria (Kebbi)
Date: Thu 6 Dec 2012
Source: The Daily Times [edited]
http://dailytimes.com.ng/article/measles-kills-5-kebbi


An outbreak of measles in the Ambursa/Kardi Development Area in Kebbi State has caused the deaths of 5 children and isolation of 187 others. An official of the Primary Health Care (PHC) in the area, Isa Abubakar, told journalists in Ambursa on Thu 6 Dec 2012 that, initially, 192 children were afflicted by the disease. He said that state, federal, and international agencies had intervened to curtail the spread of the disease and provide drugs to victims.

The Chairman of Birnin Kebbi Local Government Area, Musa Dan-Illelah, who inspected the isolation camp and victims in Ambursa, lamented the deaths of the children because of the scourge. He said that efforts would be intensified to ensure the prevention of the spread of the disease to other communities in the state, especially immunisation of children against the 6 killer diseases[?]. He said that drugs and medical facilities would be provided at the designated place of isolation for the victims.

[Byline: Chidi Okoye]

